# TypeScript Coding Standards

## Type Definitions

- Use Zod for runtime type validation, reference [src/types/swagger.ts](mdc:src/types/swagger.ts)
- Prefer `z.infer<typeof Schema>` for type inference
- Add explicit type annotations for all function parameters and return values

## Import Conventions

- Use ES6 module syntax (`import/export`)
- Organize imports in the following order:
  1. Node.js built-in modules (`path`, `fs`, `express`)
  2. Third-party libraries (`yaml`, `zod`, `fs-extra`)
  3. Local modules (`./types/swagger`)

## Error Handling

- Wrap async operations with try-catch blocks
- Handle error responses uniformly in [src/server.ts](mdc:src/server.ts)
- Provide meaningful error messages

## Code Organization

- Break complex logic into independent functions
- Use descriptive function and variable names
- Add necessary comments to explain complex algorithms

## Async Programming

- Prefer `async/await` over Promise chains
- Ensure all async operations have appropriate error handling
